Brazilian Stock Movers: Embraer, OGX Petroleo, Panamericano

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-06-20T14:10:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/brazilian-stock-movers-embraer-ogx-petroleo-panamericano.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:56 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 0.5 percent to 61,345.66.  Banco Panamericano SA (BPNM4 BS) slumped 2.9 percent to
5.63 reais. Controlling shareholder Banco BTG Pactual SA said it
will pay 4.89 reais per share to buy the shares outstanding of
Banco Panamericano in a public offer, according to a regulatory
filing June 17. BTG Pactual bought control of Panamericano in
January.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) advanced 0.2 percent to 12.67 reais.
The world’s fourth-largest planemaker won jet orders from
Jakarta’s PT Sriwijaya Air, Kenya Airways Ltd., Air Astana of
 Kazakhstan , Air Lease Corp. and GE Capital Aviation Services,
the company said in an e-mailed statement today. The order from
Sriwijaya includes 20 Embraer 190 jets, worth $856 million at
list price.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA (OGXP3 BS) rose 1.7
percent to 14.53 reais. The  oil company  controlled by
billionaire Eike Batista said it will probably declare its
Waikiki field commercial sooner than it expected after a test
well confirmed potential output of 40,000 barrels a day of
crude, according to a filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in  Sao Paulo  at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulous@bloomberg.net  